      • setup

        void setup(Dataset dataset,
           java.lang.Object... info)
    throws java.lang.Exception
        Setting up this testing algorithm based on specified dataset. In this current version, this method initializes the data sample for learning parameter and then calls learn(Object...) method.
        Parameters:
        dataset - specified dataset.
        info - additional parameters to set up this algorithm. This parameter is really an array of sub-parameters.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if any error raises.

      • unsetup

        void unsetup()
        Unset up this testing algorithm, which release resources used by the setup(Dataset, Object...) method. Exceptionally, for testing algorithm, after this method is called, this algorithm can be used (dependent on specific application).

      • learn

        java.lang.Object learn(java.lang.Object... info)
                throws java.lang.Exception
        Main method to learn parameters. As usual, it is called by setup(Dataset, Object...).
        Parameters:
        info - additional parameter.
        Returns:
        the parameter to be learned. Return null if learning is failed.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if any error occurs.
